WEBVTT

00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:22.750
Yolko!

00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:36.333
Asuna, I'm leaving him to you!

00:00:37.750 --> 00:00:38.750
Stop!

00:00:48.667 --> 00:00:49.667
Dammit!

00:00:54.292 --> 00:00:55.292
<i>Teleporting?</i>

00:00:55.708 --> 00:00:57.125
<i>Where's he planning to go?</i>

00:01:03.917 --> 00:01:05.042
Crap...

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:23.917
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:29.708
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:30.042 --> 00:01:40.583
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:40.917 --> 00:01:45.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:01:46.208 --> 00:01:50.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:01:50.917 --> 00:01:53.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:01:53.625 --> 00:01:58.917
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:01:59.333 --> 00:02:04.167
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:10.625
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:10.958 --> 00:02:14.583
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:14.917 --> 00:02:19.875
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:20.208 --> 00:02:25.875
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:26.792 --> 00:02:29.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:29.542 --> 00:02:34.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:38.125 --> 00:02:42.125
"Illusionary Avenger"

00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:46.708
You idiot!

00:02:46.708 --> 00:02:48.083
Stop being so reckless!

00:02:51.125 --> 00:02:53.208
Well? What happened?

00:02:54.125 --> 00:02:55.333
It was no use.

00:02:55.333 --> 00:02:56.833
He got away by teleporting...

00:02:57.917 --> 00:03:01.417
Inside the inns, we're
protected by the system.

00:03:01.417 --> 00:03:03.833
I was certain she'd be safe here.

00:03:04.917 --> 00:03:06.083
Dammit.

00:03:07.667 --> 00:03:10.542
That robe was Griselda's.

00:03:11.083 --> 00:03:13.917
It was Griselda's ghost...

00:03:14.333 --> 00:03:16.792
She's finally come to
get revenge on us!

00:03:18.292 --> 00:03:22.083
For a ghost, pulling off a safe-zone
PK would be simple, right?

00:03:24.458 --> 00:03:25.792
That was no ghost.

00:03:27.458 --> 00:03:32.583
There's got to be a systemic logic
to these two safe-zone murders.

00:03:33.083 --> 00:03:34.208
There's just got to be!

00:03:38.958 --> 00:03:43.292
I wonder if that black-robed figure
was really Griselda's ghost?

00:03:44.250 --> 00:03:47.333
Seeing those two deaths happen
right before my eyes...

00:03:47.333 --> 00:03:49.458
even I'm starting
to think it's true.

00:03:49.458 --> 00:03:52.542
No, that kind of thing
could never happen.

00:03:53.417 --> 00:03:57.625
In the first place, a ghost wouldn't
have had to use a teleport crystal...

00:03:58.125 --> 00:03:59.583
A teleport crystal...

00:03:59.583 --> 00:04:00.583
What is it?

00:04:02.333 --> 00:04:04.375
No, it's nothing.

00:04:14.125 --> 00:04:15.125
Here.

00:04:16.333 --> 00:04:17.917
You're giving it to me?

00:04:17.917 --> 00:04:20.708
What else would I be doing?

00:04:20.708 --> 00:04:22.458
You think I'm showing
it off or something?

00:04:22.458 --> 00:04:24.458
U-Uh, then thanks.

00:04:26.125 --> 00:04:28.750
Its durability is nearly at zero,

00:04:28.750 --> 00:04:31.000
so you should eat up
before it disappears.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:32.917
Y-Yeah.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:39.500
This is really good.

00:04:41.917 --> 00:04:44.500
When did you find the
time to pick up lunch?

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:47.208
Didn't I say their durability
was about to run out?

00:04:47.208 --> 00:04:49.125
I thought something like
this might happen,

00:04:49.125 --> 00:04:50.583
so I prepared them this morning.

00:04:51.625 --> 00:04:55.958
Gotta hand it to the leader of the attack
unit of the Knights of the Blood Oath.

00:04:55.958 --> 00:04:57.583
Where did you get these, anyway?

00:04:57.583 --> 00:04:58.750
They're not for sale.

00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:01.917
They didn't come from a store.

00:05:01.917 --> 00:05:04.292
Even I can cook, you know.

00:05:07.417 --> 00:05:10.417
W-Well, what can I say? Um...

00:05:10.417 --> 00:05:14.042
You could've just put this up for auction
and made yourself a lot of money.

00:05:20.917 --> 00:05:23.000
There are no second
helpings, all right?

00:05:28.083 --> 00:05:29.250
What's wrong?

00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.792
That's right... That's it!

00:05:36.292 --> 00:05:37.458
What?

00:05:37.458 --> 00:05:39.208
What on earth did
you just figure out?

00:05:39.208 --> 00:05:40.500
I...

00:05:40.500 --> 00:05:41.625
We...

00:05:42.042 --> 00:05:44.000
...never actually saw a thing.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.875
We just thought we did.
But we really saw something else.

00:05:48.083 --> 00:05:49.667
There never was a weapon

00:05:49.667 --> 00:05:52.792
or any kind of logic

00:05:52.792 --> 00:05:54.917
that would allow killing
within the safe areas!

00:05:57.750 --> 00:05:59.708
"Floor 19: Cross Hill"

00:05:59.708 --> 00:06:01.250
"Floor 19: Cross Hill"
Griselda...

00:06:01.833 --> 00:06:05.500
The only way I can be saved
now is if you forgive me.

00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:09.708
I'm sorry... I'm so sorry!

00:06:09.708 --> 00:06:11.125
Forgive me, Griselda!

00:06:11.833 --> 00:06:16.125
I never imagined that something
like that would happen!

00:06:19.875 --> 00:06:21.125
Really?

00:06:24.042 --> 00:06:27.542
Really? Really?

00:06:47.417 --> 00:06:50.750
What did you do to me?

00:06:51.583 --> 00:06:54.208
What did you do, Schmitt?

00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:58.125
I... I only...

00:06:58.125 --> 00:06:59.917
The day we decided to sell the ring,

00:06:59.917 --> 00:07:02.708
a note and crystal just appeared
in my belt pouch,

00:07:02.708 --> 00:07:03.833
and there were instructions...

00:07:03.833 --> 00:07:05.583
From who, Schmitt?

00:07:06.875 --> 00:07:08.917
Who were those instructions from?

00:07:11.833 --> 00:07:13.083
Grimlock?

00:07:13.708 --> 00:07:15.333
You're dead too?

00:07:16.208 --> 00:07:17.458
Who?

00:07:17.458 --> 00:07:19.958
Who gave you these orders?

00:07:19.958 --> 00:07:22.708
I-I don't know! That's the truth!

00:07:23.167 --> 00:07:26.625
The note just said to bind
the crystal to the room

00:07:26.625 --> 00:07:29.833
where Griselda was staying
so they could enter,

00:07:29.833 --> 00:07:33.083
and then to put the crystal in
the guild's shared storage...

00:07:33.083 --> 00:07:34.833
And?

00:07:34.833 --> 00:07:37.125
That was all I did!

00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:40.750
I really never meant to help
them with the murder.

00:07:41.083 --> 00:07:43.042
Believe me... Please!

00:07:50.500 --> 00:07:52.833
We recorded all of that, Schmitt.

00:08:03.083 --> 00:08:04.792
Th-They're alive?

00:08:05.250 --> 00:08:06.750
Yeah, they're alive.

00:08:07.292 --> 00:08:09.167
Both Yolko and Kains.

00:08:09.583 --> 00:08:11.042
B-But...

00:08:11.042 --> 00:08:14.333
Inside a safe zone, player HP
basically never drops.

00:08:14.333 --> 00:08:16.958
But an object's durability will.

00:08:17.292 --> 00:08:19.333
Like with that baguette
sandwich just now.

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:24.333
That day, Kains's armor
was pierced by that spear.

00:08:24.333 --> 00:08:29.208
The spear was draining the armor's
durability, not Kains's HP.

00:08:29.542 --> 00:08:32.667
Th-Then what fell apart
and scattered was...

00:08:32.667 --> 00:08:35.167
Right, it was just his armor.

00:08:35.625 --> 00:08:38.667
And at the exact moment
his armor was destroyed,

00:08:38.667 --> 00:08:42.625
Kains used a crystal to
teleport away from inside it.

00:08:43.958 --> 00:08:48.292
The effect was incredibly similar
to that of someone's death.

00:08:48.292 --> 00:08:50.250
But it's still totally different.

00:08:52.167 --> 00:08:53.833
Then Yolko...

00:08:53.833 --> 00:08:58.417
The dagger was already in her the
whole time she spoke with us.

00:08:58.417 --> 00:08:59.833
The entire time?

00:08:59.833 --> 00:09:01.375
Remember...

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:06.042
While she was in that room,
she never once turned her back to us.

00:09:06.333 --> 00:09:10.458
And as she talked, she kept an eye
on her equipment's durability level.

00:09:11.042 --> 00:09:12.417
At the right moment,

00:09:12.625 --> 00:09:16.375
she acted as though a dagger
thrown from outside had stabbed her.

00:09:17.417 --> 00:09:19.667
Which means the person
in the black robe...

00:09:19.958 --> 00:09:22.500
I'd lay good odds that
it wasn't Grimlock.

00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:23.625
It was Kains.

00:09:24.292 --> 00:09:27.375
Those two must have realized

00:09:27.375 --> 00:09:30.167
that they could use this method
to fake their own deaths.

00:09:30.583 --> 00:09:34.458
And they could add a horrific twist
like the safe zone murders.

00:09:34.458 --> 00:09:38.583
And their goal was to close in on
the culprit behind the ring murder,

00:09:38.583 --> 00:09:40.000
and expose him.

00:09:40.458 --> 00:09:43.167
Those two faked their own murders

00:09:43.167 --> 00:09:45.500
to create an illusionary avenger.

00:09:46.083 --> 00:09:50.125
They must have already been
somewhat suspicious of Schmitt.

00:09:50.583 --> 00:09:54.417
Hey, you still have Yolko
on your friend list, right?

00:09:58.250 --> 00:10:00.917
Right now, she's in
the field, on floor 19.

00:10:00.917 --> 00:10:04.417
On a small hill, just outside the town.

00:10:04.417 --> 00:10:05.458
I see.

00:10:06.750 --> 00:10:08.042
Anyway,

00:10:08.042 --> 00:10:10.042
let's let them handle the rest.

00:10:10.042 --> 00:10:12.958
Our role in this case is finished.

00:10:20.667 --> 00:10:23.708
R-Recorded?

00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:28.708
So that's how it is.

00:10:29.667 --> 00:10:33.250
You cared that much about Griselda.

00:10:33.250 --> 00:10:36.958
You didn't hate her either, did you?

00:10:36.958 --> 00:10:39.625
O-Of course not... Believe me!

00:10:39.792 --> 00:10:40.833
Sure...

00:10:40.833 --> 00:10:43.583
The rare weapon I bought
with the money I received

00:10:43.583 --> 00:10:47.667
did help me clear the Holy Dragon
Alliance's entry requirements, but...

00:10:57.583 --> 00:10:58.750
<i>Paralysis?</i>

00:11:00.958 --> 00:11:03.958
One down!

00:11:07.083 --> 00:11:09.333
<i>Don't tell me these guys are...</i>

00:11:10.667 --> 00:11:13.542
This is quite a huge catch.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:16.792
He's one of Holy Dragon
Alliance's higher-ups.

00:11:23.542 --> 00:11:26.917
<i>The murder guild,</i>
<i>Laughing Coffin.</i>

00:11:33.042 --> 00:11:36.208
Now then... what
game shall we play?

00:11:36.208 --> 00:11:38.750
That game! Let's play
that game, boss...

00:11:38.750 --> 00:11:42.083
The game where they kill each other,
and only the winner survives!

00:11:42.083 --> 00:11:46.292
You say that, but... last time we did,
you killed the survivor anyway.

00:11:47.083 --> 00:11:50.417
You can't tell them that now!
It won't be a game anymore, boss!

00:11:54.333 --> 00:11:55.625
All right.

00:11:56.292 --> 00:11:58.208
Let's get started.

00:12:20.708 --> 00:12:21.708
Ow!

00:12:23.792 --> 00:12:25.958
Guess I made it just in time...

00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:32.250
So what are you gonna do?

00:12:32.250 --> 00:12:34.625
I've got backup on the way.

00:12:34.625 --> 00:12:37.667
You want to fight 30 people
from the Assault Team?

00:12:55.333 --> 00:12:56.417
Let's go.

00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:14.500
I'm glad I was able to
see you again, Yolko.

00:13:15.625 --> 00:13:19.625
I was going to apologize to you
properly, once everything was over.

00:13:20.292 --> 00:13:22.792
But I can't expect you to believe me.

00:13:23.875 --> 00:13:25.042
Kirito...

00:13:25.542 --> 00:13:27.792
Thank you for saving me,

00:13:27.792 --> 00:13:31.875
but how did you figure it out?
That those three would attack us here?

00:13:31.875 --> 00:13:33.875
It's not like I figured it out.

00:13:33.875 --> 00:13:35.667
I just guessed that it
could be a possibility.

00:13:36.125 --> 00:13:38.333
Hey, Kains... Yolko.

00:13:38.333 --> 00:13:42.875
You asked Grimlock to make
those two weapons for you, didn't you?

00:13:44.875 --> 00:13:47.958
At first, he didn't really
seem up for it.

00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:52.000
He said he wanted to let
Griselda rest in peace...

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:54.542
But when we begged him,

00:13:54.542 --> 00:13:56.458
he finally forged the
weapons for us.

00:13:57.167 --> 00:14:00.250
I'm sorry, but the reason
he opposed your plan

00:14:00.250 --> 00:14:01.958
wasn't for Griselda's sake.

00:14:03.125 --> 00:14:06.375
He thought that staging a dramatic
incident like a safe-zone PK

00:14:06.375 --> 00:14:10.708
would draw too much attention,
and someone was bound to figure it out.

00:14:11.917 --> 00:14:14.625
I only realized it 30
minutes ago myself.

00:14:18.125 --> 00:14:21.292
We ended up playing right
into Yolko's hands...

00:14:21.292 --> 00:14:24.000
But I don't really mind.

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:25.000
Me neither.

00:14:26.625 --> 00:14:27.625
Hey.

00:14:28.792 --> 00:14:30.458
If it were you,

00:14:30.458 --> 00:14:34.000
what would you have said when
a super-rare item like that dropped?

00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:35.917
Let's see...

00:14:35.917 --> 00:14:40.542
Part of the reason I play solo
is to avoid those situations.

00:14:40.542 --> 00:14:42.958
In our guild, it would belong
to the person who got the drop.

00:14:44.583 --> 00:14:46.583
Those are the rules we play by.

00:14:46.583 --> 00:14:47.750
You know how in SAO,

00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:51.625
no one knows what items dropped
for whom unless it's self-reported?

00:14:51.625 --> 00:14:55.792
It's the only way to avoid having
players secretly hoard stuff.

00:14:55.792 --> 00:14:58.875
Also, it's because of that system

00:14:58.875 --> 00:15:01.208
that marriage in this world
has real meaning.

00:15:02.125 --> 00:15:06.333
If you marry, your item
storage is shared, right?

00:15:06.333 --> 00:15:09.292
Until then, you could've hidden
whatever you wanted, but...

00:15:09.292 --> 00:15:11.542
Once you're married,
you can't hide it anymore.

00:15:13.167 --> 00:15:17.375
Shared storage is quite a
pragmatic system.

00:15:17.375 --> 00:15:20.167
But at the same time, I think
it's very romantic as well.

00:15:23.167 --> 00:15:24.083
Hey...

00:15:24.083 --> 00:15:25.083
What?

00:15:26.458 --> 00:15:29.708
Asuna... Have you
ever gotten married?

00:15:32.458 --> 00:15:34.375
No... That's not what I meant!

00:15:34.375 --> 00:15:37.417
You were just talking about how
it's romantic and plastic...

00:15:37.417 --> 00:15:39.083
No one said that!

00:15:39.958 --> 00:15:42.750
I said it's romantic and pragmatic.

00:15:42.750 --> 00:15:46.083
Pragmatic... It means practical
for your information!

00:15:46.083 --> 00:15:47.083
Practical.

00:15:47.083 --> 00:15:48.500
Practical?

00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:50.375
Marriage in SAO?

00:15:50.375 --> 00:15:51.250
That's right!

00:15:51.250 --> 00:15:53.292
Because in a way, it throws
everything out there, doesn't it?

00:15:53.292 --> 00:15:54.875
Something like common storage.

00:15:56.500 --> 00:15:57.542
What?

00:15:57.917 --> 00:16:00.750
Common storage...

00:16:01.292 --> 00:16:04.583
If your spouse dies,
what happens to the items?

00:16:05.625 --> 00:16:08.375
Item storage is shared.

00:16:08.375 --> 00:16:11.333
When one person dies,
what happens to their items?

00:16:12.042 --> 00:16:14.542
Are you talking about
Griselda and Grimlock?

00:16:14.542 --> 00:16:17.292
Let's see, if one of them died...

00:16:17.292 --> 00:16:20.167
Wouldn't everything go to the other?

00:16:21.458 --> 00:16:24.917
Which would mean the rare ring
in Griselda's storage...

00:16:25.167 --> 00:16:29.917
It should still be in her spouse
Grimlock's storage, not in the killer's.

00:16:30.542 --> 00:16:33.417
The ring wasn't stolen?

00:16:33.417 --> 00:16:35.000
No, it was stolen.

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:36.917
It should still be
considered stolen.

00:16:36.917 --> 00:16:40.458
Grimlock stole the ring
from his own storage.

00:16:45.250 --> 00:16:47.375
It was Grimlock?

00:16:47.375 --> 00:16:49.875
He's the one who sent that memo?

00:16:49.875 --> 00:16:52.083
And he killed Griselda?

00:16:52.083 --> 00:16:55.083
No, he probably didn't do it personally.

00:16:55.083 --> 00:16:57.417
He likely left the actual murder

00:16:57.417 --> 00:16:59.792
to a red player specializing
in such villainous acts.

00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:02.542
No...

00:17:02.542 --> 00:17:04.792
If he's the real killer,

00:17:04.792 --> 00:17:08.125
then why would he have helped us?

00:17:08.125 --> 00:17:12.167
You explained the whole
plan to him, didn't you?

00:17:13.250 --> 00:17:16.167
So this was his chance to
use it to his advantage

00:17:16.167 --> 00:17:18.625
and bury the ring incident
once and for all.

00:17:19.333 --> 00:17:24.208
He just had to wait for you,
Schmitt, and Kains to gather,

00:17:24.208 --> 00:17:26.375
so he could kill you all at once.

00:17:27.458 --> 00:17:29.500
So that's why...

00:17:29.917 --> 00:17:32.458
That's why that murder
guild came here.

00:17:32.958 --> 00:17:34.250
Most likely,

00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:38.167
he knew them from when he
hired them to kill Griselda.

00:17:38.833 --> 00:17:40.042
That's horrible...

00:17:42.875 --> 00:17:44.333
I found him.

00:17:48.750 --> 00:17:51.500
We can ask him for the details.

00:17:55.917 --> 00:17:59.000
It's been a long time, everyone.

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.000
Grimlock...

00:18:01.792 --> 00:18:05.042
Did you... Did you really...

00:18:07.208 --> 00:18:08.875
Why, Grimlock?

00:18:08.875 --> 00:18:10.917
Why did you need the money

00:18:10.917 --> 00:18:14.667
from the ring so badly that you had
to kill Griselda, your own wife?

00:18:17.333 --> 00:18:18.333
Money?

00:18:19.042 --> 00:18:20.125
Did you say money?

00:18:26.250 --> 00:18:28.208
It wasn't for the money.

00:18:28.208 --> 00:18:29.333
I had...

00:18:29.333 --> 00:18:32.458
I had to kill her, no matter what...

00:18:33.125 --> 00:18:36.000
While she was still my wife.

00:18:36.917 --> 00:18:39.750
She was my wife in
the real world too.

00:18:41.750 --> 00:18:44.958
The ideal wife, the perfect wife...

00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:46.792
Pretty, submissive...

00:18:47.208 --> 00:18:50.333
We never had a single fight.

00:18:50.833 --> 00:18:54.208
But when we were both
trapped in this world,

00:18:54.750 --> 00:18:56.500
she changed.

00:18:57.333 --> 00:18:59.500
Only I was scared,
overcome by fear,

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:02.417
cowered at this death game
we were forced to play.

00:19:03.333 --> 00:19:05.875
She looked so much more alive,

00:19:05.875 --> 00:19:08.708
more fulfilled than she ever
was in the real world.

00:19:09.875 --> 00:19:12.333
I had no choice but to accept it...

00:19:12.708 --> 00:19:15.417
That the Yuko I loved was gone.

00:19:17.333 --> 00:19:18.333
Therefore...

00:19:18.833 --> 00:19:23.458
Therefore, I wanted to seal Yuko
within my memories forever...

00:19:23.458 --> 00:19:27.583
while we were still in this world
where murder is legal...

00:19:27.583 --> 00:19:29.083
And who could blame me?

00:19:30.250 --> 00:19:33.833
You killed your wife for that reason?

00:19:33.833 --> 00:19:35.792
It's more than enough reason.

00:19:36.292 --> 00:19:38.833
Someday, you'll understand
too, detective.

00:19:39.292 --> 00:19:43.292
Once you've found love and
are about to lose it, that is.

00:19:44.917 --> 00:19:48.625
No, you're the one who's
mistaken, Grimlock.

00:19:49.667 --> 00:19:52.792
What you felt for
Griselda wasn't love.

00:19:53.167 --> 00:19:55.792
The only feeling you had
for her was possessiveness!

00:20:08.875 --> 00:20:13.833
Kirito, could you let us deal
with this man ourselves?

00:20:13.833 --> 00:20:14.917
All right.

00:20:33.083 --> 00:20:34.083
Hey...

00:20:35.167 --> 00:20:39.333
If it were you... Let's say that
after you married someone,

00:20:39.333 --> 00:20:42.083
you discovered she had a side
that you didn't know about...

00:20:42.708 --> 00:20:44.250
What would you think?

00:20:46.417 --> 00:20:49.208
Maybe that I was lucky...

00:20:49.583 --> 00:20:52.792
B-Because if you marry someone,
it means you already

00:20:52.792 --> 00:20:55.708
like what you know
about them, right?

00:20:55.708 --> 00:20:58.375
So if you found something
new about them

00:20:58.375 --> 00:20:59.958
and fell in love with that too...

00:20:59.958 --> 00:21:01.625
W-Wouldn't that be great?

00:21:03.292 --> 00:21:05.042
Well, fine.

00:21:05.042 --> 00:21:07.167
Never mind that. I'm hungry.

00:21:07.583 --> 00:21:09.417
I didn't get to finish
my meal earlier.

00:21:09.833 --> 00:21:12.000
Y-Yeah...

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:14.375
We've been away from the front
lines for two whole days...

00:21:14.375 --> 00:21:16.250
We'll have to get back
to work tomorrow.

00:21:16.583 --> 00:21:20.333
Yeah, I want to clear
this floor this week.

00:21:22.750 --> 00:21:23.917
What?

00:21:56.833 --> 00:21:58.208
Hey, Kirito...

00:21:58.667 --> 00:22:00.417
Want to friend me?

00:22:01.417 --> 00:22:03.333
You haven't so far, right?

00:22:03.333 --> 00:22:04.667
Since we're both on
the Assault Team,

00:22:04.667 --> 00:22:06.833
it's inconvenient that we
can't contact each other.

00:22:06.833 --> 00:22:09.417
But I'm a solo player...

00:22:09.417 --> 00:22:12.000
I didn't say you had
to party up with me.

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:14.083
And besides, you should
make some friends at least.

00:22:14.083 --> 00:22:15.500
Sh-Should I?

00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:17.000
It's not inconvenient, but...

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:19.875
Think about it while we're eating.

00:22:19.875 --> 00:22:22.250
Okay! First, why don't we
head back to town?

00:22:22.625 --> 00:22:24.250
Y-Yeah...

00:22:30.125 --> 00:22:41.583
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.917 --> 00:22:53.458
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:59.417
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.208
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.625 --> 00:23:10.625
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.958 --> 00:23:15.917
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:22.708
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.042 --> 00:23:26.667
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.250 --> 00:23:34.000
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:39.792
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.125 --> 00:23:46.292
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.152
Next Time: "The Temperature of the Heart."
